The BuildAtlasOffline.sh script:

> Gives the options to apply patches automatically.

> Gives the option to build one or all project. (excluding tdaq and dqm)

> Creates the BuildSetup.sh scripts in each projects "home" folder.

> Runs the build script located in ./scripts/BuildInOrder.sh

	> Should you want a "make clean" or add in the debug symbols (count on about 10-20 times mores space needed) you can do this in BuildInOrder.sh, change accordingly.

